    <section id="about">
      <div class="about-container">
        <h2>About Book Haven</h2>
        <p><strong>Book Haven</strong> is a community-driven initiative focused on creating high-quality editions of public domain ebooks. These books are meticulously formatted, open-source, free of copyright restrictions in the U.S., and available at no cost.</p>

        <p>Much like other ebook projects, such as Project Gutenberg, we provide access to a wide range of ebooks for various reading devices. However, <strong>Book Haven</strong> goes a step further by refining these ebooks sourced from platforms like Project Gutenberg. Our team of volunteers carefully formats and typesets each book according to a professional-grade style manual, ensuring accuracy and a polished look. After thorough proofreading and corrections, we create new editions optimized for modern ereaders and browsers.</p>

        <p>At <strong>Book Haven</strong>, we believe that ebooks should not only be accessible and free but also beautifully crafted. These editions are not just wonderful additions to your digital library—they set a new standard for quality and design in ebook creation.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="difference">
      <div class="difference-container">
        <h2>What Makes Book Heaven Ebooks Different?</h2>
        <p class="intro-text">Modern & consistent typography</p>
        <p>Other free ebooks don't put much effort into professional-quality typography: they use "straight" quotes instead of “curly” quotes, they ignore details like em- and en-dashes, and they look more like early-90's web pages instead of actual books.</p>
        <p>Book Heaven Ebooks applies a rigorous and modern style manual when developing each and every ebook to ensure they meet a professional-grade and consistent typographical standard. Our ebooks look good.</p>

